A TreeMap in Java is a part of the java.util package that implements the Map interface. It stores key-value pairs in a sorted order using either a natural or custom comparator.
‚Ä¢ TreeMap internally uses a Red-Black Tree for efficient sorting.
‚Ä¢ Provides O(log n) time for insertion, deletion and lookup due to its self-balancing Red-Black Tree structure.
‚Ä¢ TreeMap does not allow null keys, but allows null values.


